UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1841
1 AN ACT relating to hemp-derived vapor products.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 438 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Hemp-derived vapor product" means a vapor product containing delta-8
7 tetrahydrocannabinol or delta-9 tetrahydrocannabinol that is derived from
8 hemp, as defined in KRS 260.850;
9 (b) "Retailer" means any person who sells hemp-derived vapor products to a
10 consumer for any purpose other than resale; and
11 (c) 1. "Vapor product" means any noncombustible product that employs a
12 heating element, battery, power source, electronic circuit, or other
13 electronic, chemical, or mechanical means, regardless of shape or size
14 and including the component parts and accessories thereto, that can
15 be used to deliver vaporized hemp or other substances to users
16 inhaling from the device.
17 2. "Vapor product" includes but is not limited to vape pens, disposable
18 vapes, pod systems, pod mods, or similar products or devices and every
19 variation thereof, regardless of whether marketed as such, and any
20 vapor cartridge or other container of a liquid solution or other
21 material that is intended to be used with or in vape pens, disposable
22 vapes, pod systems, pod mods, or other similar products or devices.
23 (2) (a) A retailer shall notify a consumer placing an order for any hemp-derived
24 vapor product that the shipment or delivery shall not be completed unless
25 the recipient of the shipment or delivery provides a valid identification
26 document at the time of the shipment or delivery verifying that the recipient
27 is at least twenty-one (21) years of age.
Page 1 of 3
